reviews.text:
Mixed 50/50, steeped 10 days. If classy had a taste, this would be it. I get a huge amount of gorgeous old school tobacco flavor from only 5.5% of flavoring. Never smoked a pipe in real life, so this is my introduction. The Black for Pipe gives a dark pipe tobacco taste with dark fruit (I'm reminded of plum skin) and every once in a while some maple. The TA and DNB add balls and heartiness. I feel like I'm hanging in the back of an exclusive club with Al Capone, swinging shady business deals.&#xD;
&#xD;
Do yourself a service and mix up some of ChemicalBurnVictim's recipes, even if you don't often mix with tobaccos. He did the work for you, so you can just sit back and enjoy. Thanks, Chem!
